<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8605> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8605" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 738, footnote 118" ;
	dprr:hasID 8605 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7515> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7515" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 131. Sumner (Orators 52) notes that election as quaestor in 152 for office in 151 may be the meaning of Val. Max. 2.2.1. Aedile 142? See MRR 1.475, 476, note 2. It could be dated within the period up to 137 (Sumner, loc. cit.).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7515 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3199> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3199" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Vell. 2.4.1) in Asia. Defeated, captured and killed by the forces of Aristonicus near Leucae (Liv. Per. 59; Strab. 14.1.38, 646c; Vell. 2.4.1; Val. Max. 3.2.12; Ascon. 25 C; Frontin. Str. 4.5.16; Flor. 1.35.4; Gell. 1.13.11-13; Iustin. 36.4.8; Eutrop. 4.20; Oros. 5.10.3-4)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3199 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3186> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3186" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 126, 470f. (P. Lici[ni]us P. f. P. n. Cr[- - - -], L. Valeri[us - - - -]); Chr. 354 (Muciano et Flacco); Fast. Hyd. (Crasso et Flacco), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. As Pontifex Maximus Licinius restrained his colleague, who was Flamen Martialis, from leaving the city (Cic. Phil. 11.18), then himself took command of the war against Aristonicus in Asia (Liv. Per. 59; Strabo 14.1.38; Gell. 1.13.11-13; Iustin. 36.4.7-8; Eutrop. 4.20; Oros. 5.10.1-2; Eustath. Hom. Od. 18.7; cf. CIG 2501- JOEAI 11 [1908] 69f., P. Val. ? Crassus; Val. Max. 8.7.6; Quintil. Inst. Or. 11.2.50). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 41, no. 23." ;
	dprr:hasID 3186 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3185> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3185" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "P. Licinius Crassus Dives Mucianus succeeded P. Cornelius Scipio Nasica Serapio as pontifex maximus. Cic. Phil. 11.18; Liv. Per. 59; Ascon. 25 C; Gell. 1.13.10; Oros. 5.10.1." ;
	dprr:hasID 3185 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3164> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3164" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected to the place of Ti. Gracchus (Plut. TG 21.1; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.639-642 and 719; Ann. Epig. 1945, no. 25; Auct. Vir. Ill. 65.4, C. Crassum)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3164 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3139> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3139" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest date possible for their praetorships under the Lex Villia." ;
	dprr:hasID 3139 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3043> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3043" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. De Or. 1.239-240." ;
	dprr:hasID 3043 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3042> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3042" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Mucianus' aedileship must be dated between Galba's consulship in 144 (Cic.) and the regular interval before his own praetorship (by 134), and probably, since he was a plebeian, in one of the even years 142, 140, or 138 (but see Seidel 41). Münzer (RE, and APF 264-266) accepts 142 because of his political and family connections, and believes that Cic. Off. 2.57 refers to this aedileship, not that of the Consul of 97. See 102, Aediles; Seidel, FA 44." ;
	dprr:hasID 3042 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2912> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2912" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Held this office three years before the Third Punic War (Val. Max. 2.2.1)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2912 .
